column32: It was Thursday and a workday, less busy potentially. Less vandalism on residential areas.
column40:
Litter is present in most areas of the street, concentrated in the openings of alleyways, edges of the green space and a long the sidewalks. 

Vandalism is present on the exterior of some shops that are facing alleys or streets, and is also present on street furniture.

Street furniture is filthy and covered in the remnants of old brochures. Benches and tables are chipped and worn, and there is little evidence of maintenance on them.

Greenspace is maintained and mowed, but litter is present in the form of cigarette butts and cans. Greenspace is dying in some areas, withered and unattended to.
there is litter behind the benches under the a tree and tgere are also cigarette butts on the ground. next to the quickie and there is a dog park nearby

column32: For all of elgin Street litter is most evident in low income areas or where homeless are present. Outside important government buildings it is clean.
Was not too busy when we went as it was Thursday. Busier days could have an impact on littering (?)
column40:
This area has some alleyways and was filled with both commercial and residential land use buildings.

There was litter along the sidewalks and inside corners between shops. Cans, cigarettes, a few e cigarettes, etc.

Graffiti on the side of shop walls, on the sidewalk etc

Street furniture was in attended to and had litter and vandalism on them.

column32: The street was not very busy being a workday (Thursday) so less people were there to litter.
column40:
First stretch of road towards Gladstone, filled with tidy commercial areas. Almost no greenspace

Litter was present but there was minimal and it was scattered across the side of the road.

Vandalism was not present anywhere.

Street furniture was covered in the remnants of old brochures, garbage bins were slightly dirty.

Greenspace was present but there was not a lot of it, and the trees that were present were withered at the base.
